metadata.name: Smoke #51
metadata.description:
Inspired by the hot weather of the city.
Made in August 2022, Milano, Italy.

5 visible Features:
-Mood: tender, bleed, icecream, summer in Milano, evening, futurepunk, acid, love
-Size: small, regular, big
-Density: low, moderate, high, very high
-Speed: slow, moderate, fast
-Emissions: from 2 to 9

Some of the features are very rare, others less, some more common.

The design is being optimized to render at different speeds depending on the size of the window. The smaller the size, the faster the render and lower the detail, viceversa bigger the size, slower the render and higher the detail.
The moire effect of lines that are making the shades of the artwork will look thick with a low resolution, and become finer and more detailed the higher the resolution. You can use this feature to create quick previews or to save very Hi-Resolution images.
To save an image with the size of the window press S once the image is fully rendered.
The fx(hash) thumbnail is saved at 1425px x 1900px.
To save a Hi-Resolution image 3000px x 4000px press H and wait, the page will reload and start to render. Please be patient.

Built using p5js, published under CC-BY-NC-4.0 license.

Once the collection will be fully minted, the variations button will be disabled.

metadata.name: rememberance #8
metadata.description:
A field of slit-scan flowers, created from slicing images from my "abstracted expressions" acrylic painting/collage series, minted on exchange.art ( https://exchange.art/series/abstracted%20expression/nfts ). I have been looking for a way to bridge my code-based art on Tezos with my physical art on Solana, and this is an attempt to do so. 

The 9 paintings used in the piece are all acrylic, charcoal, wax pastel, and collage on paper, scanned at 600dpi. The FxHash mint is coded in p5.js

metadata.name: GEN XYZ Das Occult #1566
metadata.description:
A 10k Generative Profile Pic collection
GEN XYZ Das Occult - by culla - @tamccullough

move over cryptopunks
there is a new group on the scene

100% code - not an image composition

A bunch of common palettes
A selection of rare palettes
And a smaller set of ultra rare palettes
However, rarity will be based on what combinations the code produces

The majority of tokens will not have a special trait
However your token might have one or even multiple special traits
But, be aware that only the last special trait added will be listed in the features

Even then, look closely, because not all aspects of the canvas are included in the features. Collectors should still look closely and choose what they like when buying on secondary.

Which team are you on? X or O?

follow culla on twitter for updates. Or maybe __acolyte__

If the non reserved tokens mint out quickly, Access List mints will have 24 hours to mint reserves assigned to those wallets

Thank you for supporting an emerging artist in the generative art space

Access List reserves were given to holders of the following PFP collections created by culla
2x for each Basqunk held
1x for each Inkspunk, TwoFourQunk, V0iD, DeeManz, Punkasso and CR0$$KULL
You would have needed to transfer the above tokens to your mint wallet at the time of the snapshot

share your tokens on social media with #genxyznft
Made with love by culla using p5.js

metadata.name: Primordial #207
metadata.description:
Primordial is a study of abstract forms. The algorithm, written in p5.js and WebGL, utilizes domain warping to create twisted fields of color and then overlays thousands of tiny lines to provide depth and texture. The outputs are chaotic but not completely formless, like a swirling mass of plasma from the early universe, or a strange proto-life form suspended in prehistoric ooze.

CONTROLS:

1-9: Increase resolution and save image in PNG format

B: Toggle borders on/off

F: Fullscreen
P: Portrait
L: Landscape
S: Square

For third party license information, please see license.md

David Brice Allen
October 2022

metadata.name: Holons #49
metadata.description:
Everything is divisible. Larger organisms are made up of smaller ones, entire galaxies are comprised of stars, planets, people, dust, and one effect here and now ripples into eternity. Nothing exists without the elemental components that have evolved to make them possible ‚Äî and nothing on the plane of existence arrives in isolation from something greater. This enmeshed reality is the concept of a Holon: a whole that is simultaneously part of another whole. 

As cells, energies, beings, and ideas grow in complexity, each new advancement includes and transcends their holons, the very catalysts of evolution. What does this essential process look like on its own when scale, context, and definition are removed? The senses are forced to purely observe the present interactions and reactions that occur between all parts. This is what Holons attempts to portray ‚Äî the witnessing of birth, formation, and crystallization simultaneously. 

Upon viewing each piece and inspecting its detail with curiosity ‚Äî we can observe living reality that has been temporarily suspended from motion and artificially stopped for us to witness. Can we see what is a part, and what is a whole? Can we define what these holons are? 

Let each Holons remind us that the impossible can always be made; let each one be nothing and everything ‚Äî organisms, cosmos, energy itself ‚Äî all at once, for it‚Äôs the creation of something entirely new that best reminds us that everything is actually made of the parts already here. So, remember to create without barriers or limitations because reality itself is made of that which lives now only in imagination.


--------

TENDER x flight404
October 2022

Press ‚Äòh‚Äô in live view to render a high resolution version of any token.
Press ‚Äòs‚Äô in live view to save a .png of the current view of any token.

Holons was created in vanilla Javascript and WebGL, but the majority of the work was done in GLSL shaders. This setup was substantially assisted by fx(hash) community leader and artist Liam Egan who provided technical assistance and emotional support during the project's lifespan. For this reason, we have included him in the split of proceeds.

metadata.name: Release #94
metadata.description:
[‚Ä¶]

More than anything she had wanted to show him where she had lived, where, at a specific time every year, endless fields sent a new cycle of pods on their way.

She preferred to experience these moments alone, imagining the spectacle was being performed just for her. The whole act carried a promise of new beginnings, of paths yet to be taken.

She wasn't really part of any of this, but she too had the coordinates to her own life programmed into her genes.

Any decision would be true now, any path free.

A chorus of explosions sounded as the field burst open.

metadata.name: tratti #96
metadata.description:
"tratti" is an Italian word that has many different meanings. When we started working on this piece, we wanted to create something that combines our traits ("tratti" in Italian).
We had this urge to channel the turbulent times we're living in now into this artwork using just lines ("tratti" in Italian).

We don't know what to do now, we're here, and that's all that matters. We're here for our families, our friends, and our community. Like everything in life, there are joyful times and challenging times. We must accept happiness as something that is not constant but that we feel at times (a "tratti" in Italian).

With "tratti", we want to send a message to every disheartened human being: "Stay strong and never let anyone or anything crush the hope in you. Joyful times are around the corner".
